# Python Tooling Standards

## Core Tools

- **Ruff**: Formatting and linting ([docs](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/))
- **Pyright**: Type checking ([docs](https://microsoft.github.io/pyright/))
- **uv**: Package management ([docs](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/))
- **pytest**: Testing
- **pre-commit**: Automated quality checks

## uv Commands

**CRITICAL: Always use `uv` for package management**

```bash
# ✅ Correct
uv add package-name           # Add dependency
uv add --dev package-name     # Add dev dependency
uv sync                       # Install/update dependencies
uv run moneybin --help        # Run CLI
uv run pytest tests/          # Run tests
uv run pyright src/           # Type check

# ❌ Never use
pip install package-name
uv pip install package-name
python -m pip install
pip install -e .
python -m moneybin.cli.main
```

**Why uv?**: 10-100x faster than pip, deterministic builds, integrated environment management

## Ruff

```bash
ruff format .           # Format code
ruff check .            # Check linting
ruff check --fix .      # Auto-fix issues
```

## Pyright

```bash
uv run pyright                  # Check all code
uv run pyright src/file.py      # Check specific file
```

## Pre-commit

```bash
pre-commit run              # Run on staged files
pre-commit run --all-files  # Run on all files
```

## Setup New Environment

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd moneybin
uv sync --dev
pre-commit install
uv run pytest tests/
```

## Before Committing

```bash
ruff format . && ruff check . && uv run pyright && uv run pytest tests/
```

